The Role 
The Director, Product Management (PM) proposes, builds and delivers AI products and capabilities for Fidelity business units as well as partners and customers. We provide business direction to an extended team of associates contributing heterogeneous roles. We bring to the table an outstanding blend of business, technical and team management savvyâ€”big-picture vision with the drive and knowhow to make that vision a reality. We have a passion for finding innovative, robust, algorithmic solutions to sophisticated business challenges. 
The Expertise and Skills You Bring 
10+ years of related experience across product management, engineering and business planning 
BS degree in computer science or other technical field. MBA is highly desired 
Demonstrated experience leading heterogeneous teams to deliver breakthrough results over the entire product lifecycle - from conception to full production deployment, at scale 
Proven leadership in matrixed environments where the project team is working from, and feeling motivated by, your business direction 
Demonstrated ability to build trust-based relationships â€“ within teams and across partner groups 
Demonstrated strong verbal and written communication skills; communicate across all areas and levels of the company as the primary â€˜voiceâ€™ for the team and its results 
Ability to work in a fast-paced, unexpected and frequently ambiguous environment 
Entrepreneurial drive - you are a selfstarter; strong attention to detail and ability to set and meet ambitious plans 
Proven experience with &/or interest in Artificial Intelligence concepts and applications in a business context 
Strong analytical, project management and product development process experience 
The Team 
Create ground-breaking artificial intelligence-based (AI) solutions and platforms as the leader of cross-functional teams in the Fidelity Center for Applied Technology (FCAT). Be part of the innovation engine for the Firm, creating new businesses and capabilities that continue to distinguish Fidelity as the best, and most trusted, brand in the financial services industry. 
We are seeking a product management leader who understands how to lead diverse teams to deliver breakthrough results. The role is highly visible within FCAT and Fidelity, at large. A strategic mentality is essential, in this role, to reconcile and prioritize contending demands across inter-personal, organizational and technical domains. 
See what FCAT is up to at https://www.fcatalyst.com/overview.  This position will be located full time in Durham, NC. 
